<h2>Data Source and Methodology</h2>
<p>All calculations are based on standard Fourier series formulas. For more details, see <a href="https://www.wolframalpha.com/input?i=Fourier+series+calculator" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Wolfram Alpha</a>.</p>
<h2>The Formula Explained</h2>
<p>The Fourier series of a function f(x) over the interval [a, b] is given by:</p>
<div class="formula-box">
<pre>f(x) ≈ a₀/2 + Σ [aₙ cos(nπx/L) + bₙ sin(nπx/L)], n=1 to ∞</pre>
</div>
<h2>Glossary of Terms</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Function:</strong> The mathematical expression representing the periodic function.</li>
<li><strong>Range:</strong> The interval over which the Fourier series is calculated.</li>
<li><strong>Fourier Coefficients:</strong> Constants a₀, aₙ, and bₙ that define the series.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<div>
<h3>What is the purpose of a Fourier series?</h3>
<p>A Fourier series decomposes a periodic function into a sum of simple oscillating functions, providing insights into its frequency components.</p>
<h3>Can this calculator handle complex functions?</h3>
<p>Yes, it can process complex functions, but it may not support every aspect of all functions natively. Check compatibility.</p>
